1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,383
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,383 --> 00:00:02,750
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,550 --> 00:00:05,650
(Episode 7)

4
00:00:11,150 --> 00:00:12,150
No one's here.

5
00:00:17,983 --> 00:00:19,550
Hello,

6
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:21,250
I'm here to clean this room.

7
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:22,150
Okay.

8
00:00:24,983 --> 00:00:26,750
(To discard)

9
00:00:28,850 --> 00:00:29,850
Are you okay?

10
00:00:29,850 --> 00:00:31,350
I'll clean it up right away.

11
00:00:31,350 --> 00:00:32,750
No, let's do it together.

12
00:00:33,150 --> 00:00:34,450
No, I'll handle it.

13
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:35,450
Let's do it together.

14
00:00:41,550 --> 00:00:43,050
- Hey, you jerk!
- I'm sorry.

15
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:55,983
What is wrong with this lady?

16
00:01:02,383 --> 00:01:03,383
Blood...

17
00:01:04,350 --> 00:01:06,250
Sorry? Blood?

18
00:01:13,183 --> 00:01:15,850
Lady, what do you think you are doing?

19
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:17,550
What am I doing?

20
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:20,750
I'm his daughter, so what?

21
00:01:24,350 --> 00:01:25,350
Eun Ae.

22
00:01:27,383 --> 00:01:29,183
Lucky Joy!

23
00:01:29,183 --> 00:01:31,650
So you do know who I am.

24
00:01:32,183 --> 00:01:34,483
What did you just do to my dad?

25
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:36,283
He's an elderly man,

26
00:01:36,283 --> 00:01:38,950
and you threw documents at him!

27
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:43,950
No, that's not what happened.

28
00:01:45,150 --> 00:01:46,183
I'm really sorry.

29
00:01:50,350 --> 00:01:51,650
What are you doing here?

30
00:01:52,783 --> 00:01:55,683
No, what are you doing here?
And why are you in those clothes?

31
00:01:59,550 --> 00:02:01,150
Is this how you do your work?

32
00:02:01,850 --> 00:02:02,950
Get it done quickly!

33
00:02:04,850 --> 00:02:06,150
This is insane.

34
00:02:06,950 --> 00:02:08,350
If Grandpa finds out...

35
00:02:11,450 --> 00:02:12,283
I'm sorry.

36
00:02:12,983 --> 00:02:14,183
She's my daughter.

37
00:02:14,183 --> 00:02:16,050
There seems
to have been some misunderstanding.

38
00:02:16,483 --> 00:02:17,483
Dad.

39
00:02:17,783 --> 00:02:19,350
Yes, it seems that way.

40
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:21,650
Hey, don't you remember me?

41
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:23,250
Remember you?

42
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:25,583
I made such a fuss trying to meet you,

43
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:26,883
but you never once showed your face,

44
00:02:26,883 --> 00:02:28,416
so how am I supposed to remember you?

45
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:31,183
How did you even get in here?

46
00:02:31,183 --> 00:02:32,350
Dad, let's talk later.

47
00:02:32,983 --> 00:02:35,150
Let go!
I have something to discuss with the CPO!

48
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:36,350
Eun Ae!

49
00:02:40,583 --> 00:02:41,583
I'm really sorry.

50
00:02:42,650 --> 00:02:44,250
I'll start by cleaning this up.

51
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:45,250
Yes.

52
00:02:49,883 --> 00:02:51,750
Gyeol, what happened to this room?

53
00:02:53,483 --> 00:02:55,683
And what happened to your face?
What's going on?

54
00:02:55,683 --> 00:02:56,850
It's nothing.

55
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,250
This is not nothing.

56
00:03:00,483 --> 00:03:02,250
Excuse me.

57
00:03:02,350 --> 00:03:03,983
What are you doing? Clean this up quickly.

58
00:03:04,150 --> 00:03:05,150
Yes, sir.

59
00:03:05,783 --> 00:03:06,783
Yes.

60
00:03:09,883 --> 00:03:11,350
Wait, are you...?

61
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:14,350
Cho Seong Jun?

62
00:03:14,850 --> 00:03:15,850
Hey, Seong Jun!

63
00:03:16,283 --> 00:03:18,650
It's me, Ko Dae Chi.
Don't you recognize me?

64
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:21,950
Hi, it's been a while.

65
00:03:26,550 --> 00:03:30,150
But why are you here doing this?

66
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:33,750
I'm on duty right now,

67
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:35,250
so let's talk later.

68
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:37,550
Okay.

69
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:40,450
I don't know what's going on,
but put this down.

70
00:03:40,450 --> 00:03:43,183
I'll have someone else take care of this,
so put it down.

71
00:03:43,850 --> 00:03:46,850
Hey, how long has it been?

72
00:03:53,783 --> 00:03:56,650
He's my high school friend. Say hello.

73
00:03:59,350 --> 00:04:01,050
Hello, I'm Ko Gyeol.

74
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,750
Hello.

75
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,850
- I'm really sorry.
- No need to apologize.

76
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:08,883
He's my son. Why apologize?

77
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:11,250
Come on, let's go.

78
00:04:11,250 --> 00:04:14,050
Let's go to my office and talk properly.

79
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:16,950
Hold on, let me just make one quick call.

80
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:19,350
Mr. Seo, it's me.

81
00:04:19,350 --> 00:04:20,550
Get to my office right now.

82
00:04:21,283 --> 00:04:22,750
If I tell you to come, just come.
Stop talking.

83
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:24,950
Come, hurry. Seong Jun.

84
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:39,750
I just want to discuss work with the CPO.

85
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:41,050
Why are you all acting like this?

86
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:43,050
Because of you,
we're all going to get fired!

87
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:44,250
Please leave!

88
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:46,850
I'm not a suspicious person.

89
00:04:46,850 --> 00:04:49,283
I'm the developer
of the program this company acquired!

90
00:04:49,850 --> 00:04:51,350
- Let go of me!
- What's going on?

91
00:04:52,683 --> 00:04:53,883
I'll look into it
and report back right away.

92
00:04:53,883 --> 00:04:56,550
Come on, what's wrong with you? Let go!

93
00:04:58,850 --> 00:05:00,350
What's wrong with you?

94
00:05:01,283 --> 00:05:02,350
So...

95
00:05:03,050 --> 00:05:05,950
she mistook you
for the Chief Planning Officer?

96
00:05:07,650 --> 00:05:10,650
She said she's the co-CEO of Lucky Joy.
Is there a problem?

97
00:05:10,650 --> 00:05:12,250
What problem?

98
00:05:13,650 --> 00:05:16,450
I recently acquired a startup.

99
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:17,450
She's a developer there.

100
00:05:17,983 --> 00:05:19,850
We went through all the legal procedures.

101
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:21,250
She's completely crazy.

102
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:22,850
If everything was done properly, then why?

103
00:05:22,950 --> 00:05:24,150
That's why she's crazy.

104
00:05:25,050 --> 00:05:26,050
This won't do.

105
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:28,550
- Legal team?
- Yes.

106
00:05:28,550 --> 00:05:30,350
Tell Mr. Hwang to come up to my office.

107
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:31,350
Yes, understood.

108
00:05:32,883 --> 00:05:33,883
Anyway,

109
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:36,350
you rejected Grandpa's proposal at first.

110
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:38,450
Why the sudden change of heart?

111
00:05:39,350 --> 00:05:43,083
Do you think
a person's heart stays the same forever?

112
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:44,850
That's true.

113
00:05:45,883 --> 00:05:47,150
Since it's come to this,

114
00:05:48,483 --> 00:05:49,483
let's play fair.

115
00:05:55,150 --> 00:05:56,850
Sounds good. Fair play.

116
00:06:02,983 --> 00:06:04,383
Come in.

117
00:06:04,850 --> 00:06:06,750
Hey, Mr. Seo, come on in.

118
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:09,750
Do you recognize him?

119
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:12,550
It's Seong Jun!

120
00:06:18,783 --> 00:06:19,783
Gwon Sik.

121
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:24,150
It's been a while, Cho Seong Jun.

122
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:30,250
How did the top two students in school...

123
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:32,650
both end up at my company?

124
00:06:33,950 --> 00:06:35,250
By the way, Seong Jun,

125
00:06:35,850 --> 00:06:38,350
weren't you working at Samho Group?

126
00:06:39,550 --> 00:06:40,950
I quit last year.

127
00:06:41,583 --> 00:06:42,650
Last year, hold on a second.

128
00:06:42,650 --> 00:06:45,283
Then was it during the restructuring?

129
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:49,350
So you got hit by that.

130
00:06:50,950 --> 00:06:54,550
Let's see,
all of us getting together like this...

131
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:01,850
It's been over 40 years, right?

132
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,083
I'm busy, so I'll go now.

133
00:07:08,050 --> 00:07:09,150
I should go too,

134
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:10,850
- I'm on duty.
- Hey, wait.

135
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:13,850
Seong Jun, starting tomorrow,
change your cleaning area.

136
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:15,450
Take care of my office exclusively.

137
00:07:17,350 --> 00:07:19,650
Just take it easy
and relax while you work.

138
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:21,583
Hey, that's what friends are for.

139
00:07:22,450 --> 00:07:24,450
There's no need. I'm leaving.

140
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:28,950
Unbelievable.

141
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:30,683
Those guys...

142
00:07:31,350 --> 00:07:33,350
In the end, they're all under me,

143
00:07:33,783 --> 00:07:34,983
at my company.

144
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:37,650
This is insane.

145
00:07:40,150 --> 00:07:41,183
Why are you here...

146
00:07:42,983 --> 00:07:44,483
with Dae Chi?

147
00:07:45,650 --> 00:07:47,350
I've been serving the Chairman
for 20 years.

148
00:07:48,350 --> 00:07:49,783
I don't work under Dae Chi.

149
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:52,683
Then, since that time?

150
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:02,250
Yes, Chairman.

151
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:04,550
Are you heading home now?

152
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:07,550
Yes, I'll go right away.

153
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:11,783
You seem busy, so go ahead.

154
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:13,450
Yes, you should get back to work.

155
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:16,283
- I'll see you next time.
- Yeah.

156
00:08:30,650 --> 00:08:32,583
Eun Ae, are you okay?

157
00:08:34,783 --> 00:08:37,450
I'll be done soon, so I'll call you after.

158
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:38,750
Let's talk in person.

159
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:41,550
And don't tell Mom...

160
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:43,950
you saw me here.

161
00:08:43,950 --> 00:08:45,483
I know what you mean.

162
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:47,783
And don't you tell her about me either.

163
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:49,150
Okay.

164
00:08:52,650 --> 00:08:53,983
What on earth is going on?

165
00:08:58,950 --> 00:09:00,050
Yes, Supervisor.

166
00:09:01,350 --> 00:09:04,083
Yes, I'll be right there.

167
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,183
Did you hear?

168
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:11,750
The new TF team leader
is a very famous architect.

169
00:09:12,683 --> 00:09:16,050
Really? Where did you hear that?

170
00:09:16,050 --> 00:09:17,883
I have a friend in HR.

171
00:09:18,283 --> 00:09:19,850
And they said...

172
00:09:20,950 --> 00:09:22,550
he's the Chairman's grandson.

173
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:23,550
Ms. Ha Yu Ju,

174
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:27,450
are the briefing materials
for the new team leader ready?

175
00:09:28,350 --> 00:09:30,050
Yes, almost.

176
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:34,050
Everyone, please gather here.

177
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:35,050
Over this way.

178
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:38,650
Let me introduce you.
This is the newly appointed...

179
00:09:38,650 --> 00:09:41,650
Retirement Community TF Team Two leader
of Strategic Planning.

180
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:43,850
Nice to meet you. I'm Ko Gyeol.

181
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:46,150
I'm Assistant Manager Kim Seong Guk.
Nice to meet you.

182
00:09:47,350 --> 00:09:49,750
I'm Ha Yu Ju. I'll do my best.

183
00:09:50,550 --> 00:09:52,683
Hello, I'm Section Chief Seo Seung Ri.

184
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:55,583
Mr. Kim Seong Guk, Ms. Ha Yu Ju,

185
00:09:55,950 --> 00:09:56,983
Ms. Seo Seung Ri,

186
00:09:57,150 --> 00:09:58,150
nice to meet you.

187
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:02,883
That's enough for introductions.

188
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:05,683
This must be your desk.

189
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:07,083
I see.

190
00:10:12,683 --> 00:10:15,150
The desk just arrived,
so we didn't have time...

191
00:10:15,850 --> 00:10:17,250
I'll ask Facilities to clean it.

192
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:18,350
No, it's fine.

193
00:10:20,050 --> 00:10:22,150
No, don't worry about it.

194
00:10:22,650 --> 00:10:24,550
Cleaning is my specialty.

195
00:10:26,283 --> 00:10:28,850
Where is the break room?

196
00:10:29,550 --> 00:10:30,550
Let's do it together then.

197
00:10:32,883 --> 00:10:35,083
Ms. Seo,
may I speak with you for a moment?

198
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:45,650
About the other day,
my mother made a big mistake.

199
00:10:47,050 --> 00:10:49,150
I'm really sorry.
Let me apologize on her behalf...

200
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:51,483
No, I don't need an apology from you.

201
00:10:52,583 --> 00:10:53,783
I should apologize first.

202
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:57,250
No matter how angry I was,
I should've held myself back.

203
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:58,583
I'm sorry.

204
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:01,450
No, you had every right to be angry.

205
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:04,750
You were dragged there clueless
and had to deal with that.

206
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:06,950
If that's all, I'll be going.

207
00:11:07,483 --> 00:11:10,783
I think Gyeol can handle
the cleaning alone.

208
00:11:25,383 --> 00:11:27,550
What is all this?

209
00:11:29,850 --> 00:11:30,983
Why did you come out?

210
00:11:31,183 --> 00:11:32,750
I told you not to come out
until I called you.

211
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:36,150
Give it to me, I'll do it.

212
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:39,750
No, I'll get it right this time.

213
00:11:40,650 --> 00:11:42,950
Father, what are you doing?

214
00:11:45,450 --> 00:11:47,783
You said you had golf in the morning...

215
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:51,283
and a flower arrangement class
in the afternoon.

216
00:11:51,283 --> 00:11:55,150
Yes, but I didn't feel well,
so I skipped the class.

217
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:59,350
More importantly,
are you making a meal for Mother?

218
00:12:00,050 --> 00:12:01,250
With an apron on?

219
00:12:02,283 --> 00:12:04,250
Meal? What are you talking about?

220
00:12:05,350 --> 00:12:07,583
If you wanted something,
you could've just said so.

221
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:12,983
I'll pretend I didn't see anything.

222
00:12:13,850 --> 00:12:15,950
Please go ahead.

223
00:12:21,650 --> 00:12:23,683
You said we'd grant each other wishes.

224
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:27,150
Did you wish to prepare a meal for me?

225
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:28,850
I've spent...

226
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:32,150
my whole life eating meals you prepared,

227
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,450
so I wanted to prepare one
for you just once.

228
00:12:37,683 --> 00:12:39,350
Why the eggs?

229
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:41,450
There are plenty of side dishes.

230
00:12:42,583 --> 00:12:45,750
Don't you remember? At the diner,

231
00:12:46,783 --> 00:12:51,550
you used to put a fried egg
only on my rice.

232
00:12:52,483 --> 00:12:53,583
What?

233
00:13:01,050 --> 00:13:02,050
Thank you.

234
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:27,483
That was because...

235
00:13:27,483 --> 00:13:29,450
I owed you so much.

236
00:13:31,283 --> 00:13:33,250
You protected me from people...

237
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,850
who looked down on me as a young widow.

238
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:39,050
And sometimes...

239
00:13:40,050 --> 00:13:42,150
you brought snacks...

240
00:13:43,783 --> 00:13:44,783
and dolls for Yeon Sun.

241
00:13:49,383 --> 00:13:51,650
I'm sorry, because of me...

242
00:13:52,950 --> 00:13:54,250
There you go again.

243
00:13:55,683 --> 00:13:57,350
Hurry and eat. The soup is getting cold.

244
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:02,983
Anyway, this mission was a total failure.

245
00:14:06,850 --> 00:14:08,783
Father cooked?

246
00:14:08,783 --> 00:14:11,483
Yeah, he even wore an apron...

247
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:13,383
and cracked nearly a whole tray of eggs...

248
00:14:13,650 --> 00:14:15,950
to prepare a meal for her.

249
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:18,883
They say if a person suddenly changes,
it means death is near.

250
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:21,083
Come on, seriously...

251
00:14:21,683 --> 00:14:22,683
My mistake.

252
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:26,283
You know
I don't think things through much.

253
00:14:27,683 --> 00:14:29,950
Honey, the more you think,

254
00:14:30,683 --> 00:14:33,950
the more thoughts you'll have,

255
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:36,850
so not thinking at all is the best idea.

256
00:14:37,483 --> 00:14:38,483
My crystal.

257
00:14:38,683 --> 00:14:40,850
You even have a sense of humor.

258
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:43,883
You're exactly my type.

259
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:47,350
Honey, how about a glass of wine?
It's been a while.

260
00:14:48,783 --> 00:14:49,883
Sounds great.

261
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,183
Wait, move aside for a second.

262
00:14:52,183 --> 00:14:53,750
Hold on, honey.

263
00:15:07,383 --> 00:15:10,450
You totally look like Chow Yun Fat.

264
00:15:12,183 --> 00:15:13,850
I love you, Eun Su Jeong.

265
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:15,650
Honey, I love you.

266
00:15:15,983 --> 00:15:17,283
I love you too.

267
00:15:17,283 --> 00:15:19,150
- I love you.
- I love you.

268
00:15:37,950 --> 00:15:38,950
Why are you here...

269
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:42,350
with Dae Chi?

270
00:15:42,883 --> 00:15:44,650
I've been serving the Chairman
for 20 years.

271
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:46,750
I don't work under Dae Chi.

272
00:15:47,950 --> 00:15:49,683
Then, since that time?

273
00:16:03,283 --> 00:16:04,283
My goodness.

274
00:16:04,683 --> 00:16:07,183
The top student in school
is now working as a cleaner?

275
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:10,350
Unbelievable.

276
00:16:11,050 --> 00:16:12,483
That's what I'm saying.

277
00:16:13,050 --> 00:16:15,550
Studying doesn't matter at all.

278
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:19,650
What you're born with matters the most.

279
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:22,883
My husband was born with a silver spoon,

280
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,683
so I'm so happy.

281
00:16:34,450 --> 00:16:36,483
Honey, shall we have more wine?

282
00:16:36,883 --> 00:16:37,883
Well...

283
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,050
Father is sick and all,

284
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:42,950
but instead of holding back,
should we have one more bottle?

285
00:16:43,183 --> 00:16:45,083
- Okay.
- I'll go get the wine.

286
00:16:45,450 --> 00:16:46,950
No, honey, let's go together.

287
00:16:46,950 --> 00:16:48,650
Let's go together. I might get lost.

288
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:49,683
- Come on, let's go together.
- Let's go together.

289
00:16:52,083 --> 00:16:54,083
Son, when did you come home?

290
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:00,483
Hey, what are you doing?

291
00:17:02,883 --> 00:17:04,183
- You.
- My goodness!

292
00:17:04,183 --> 00:17:06,250
Hey, what are you doing right now?

293
00:17:10,683 --> 00:17:12,550
I'm punishing myself...

294
00:17:13,350 --> 00:17:15,250
for what you did to Seung Ri, Mother.

295
00:17:16,050 --> 00:17:17,550
I can't punish my own mother.

296
00:17:17,550 --> 00:17:19,050
What did you say?

297
00:17:19,050 --> 00:17:20,550
You little...

298
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:23,650
- Hey!
- Stop it!

299
00:17:23,650 --> 00:17:25,050
Stop it!

300
00:17:27,350 --> 00:17:28,450
Apologize to Seung Ri.

301
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:30,350
If you don't apologize,

302
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:32,883
I'll have to keep punishing myself.

303
00:17:33,850 --> 00:17:34,850
You will apologize, right?

304
00:17:34,850 --> 00:17:37,483
Are you crazy?
What did I do wrong to apologize?

305
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:39,783
All right.

306
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:41,150
Hey.

307
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:44,383
What do we do? What's wrong with you?

308
00:17:45,050 --> 00:17:46,050
Why are you...?

309
00:17:46,183 --> 00:17:47,250
If you don't apologize,

310
00:17:47,950 --> 00:17:50,250
I'll keep pouring ice water
over myself every day.

311
00:17:50,883 --> 00:17:51,883
Do you understand?

312
00:17:52,450 --> 00:17:54,850
What is wrong with you, seriously?

313
00:17:57,050 --> 00:17:58,050
Seriously.

314
00:17:59,950 --> 00:18:01,950
This is Songrim Stadium.

315
00:18:12,150 --> 00:18:13,550
Hey, you jerk!

316
00:18:18,883 --> 00:18:21,083
I might just throw this away.

317
00:18:21,083 --> 00:18:22,550
This ridiculous bracelet.

318
00:18:25,350 --> 00:18:27,783
She never listens to what I have to say.

319
00:18:29,150 --> 00:18:31,050
Seriously.

320
00:18:32,183 --> 00:18:34,250
A year ago? If it was a year ago,

321
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:36,650
that's right after you got promoted
to executive director.

322
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:39,583
Then why did they even promote you?

323
00:18:40,350 --> 00:18:43,350
Maybe they felt bad firing me
as a lifelong department head.

324
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:44,750
That's ridiculous.

325
00:18:45,450 --> 00:18:47,683
You were so devoted to the company.

326
00:18:48,850 --> 00:18:51,150
Then for the past year,

327
00:18:51,450 --> 00:18:52,850
you've been doing cleaning work?

328
00:18:53,450 --> 00:18:56,050
Not exactly. At first,

329
00:18:56,050 --> 00:18:58,750
I tried to find a job
that matched my experience.

330
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:02,350
But it wasn't as easy as I thought.

331
00:19:03,850 --> 00:19:06,183
There are so many young job seekers,

332
00:19:06,683 --> 00:19:09,783
so opportunities didn't come
to someone like me, who's nearing 60.

333
00:19:12,450 --> 00:19:14,450
That's me, but what about you?

334
00:19:20,950 --> 00:19:23,083
Dad, actually, I...

335
00:19:26,950 --> 00:19:29,950
You must've had a hard time all this time.

336
00:19:30,983 --> 00:19:33,883
It's nothing compared
to what you've been through.

337
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:37,750
But still, you just barged in like that
and caused a scene?

338
00:19:38,383 --> 00:19:39,650
With no plan?

339
00:19:39,650 --> 00:19:42,350
I was going to persuade them somehow
and get Joy back,

340
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:45,950
but the moment I saw
that CPO throw documents at you,

341
00:19:45,950 --> 00:19:47,450
I completely lost it.

342
00:19:47,450 --> 00:19:48,950
He threw documents at me?

343
00:19:50,050 --> 00:19:52,783
No, he was trying
to pick up the papers I dropped,

344
00:19:52,783 --> 00:19:55,050
and he cut his finger and let them fall.

345
00:19:55,483 --> 00:19:56,683
What? Really?

346
00:19:57,650 --> 00:19:59,983
This is bad. I didn't know that.

347
00:20:00,850 --> 00:20:03,250
I was assigned to that office
for the first time today,

348
00:20:03,483 --> 00:20:05,150
and he seemed like a decent person.

349
00:20:06,150 --> 00:20:07,883
You should apologize properly later.

350
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:10,450
What you did today was clearly an assault.

351
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:18,783
Why am I like this?

352
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:22,150
Why do I mess everything up?

353
00:20:23,450 --> 00:20:27,650
Could you get in trouble
because of what I did?

354
00:20:28,283 --> 00:20:29,983
Don't worry about me.

355
00:20:32,883 --> 00:20:34,450
I'm more worried about you.

356
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:38,383
The company you worked so hard to build,
all in one day...

357
00:20:39,550 --> 00:20:43,250
I'm sorry, Dad. I always make you worry.

358
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:47,050
No, I trust my daughter.

359
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:50,250
I trust you too.

360
00:20:50,883 --> 00:20:54,283
I know you'll get back on your feet.

361
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:59,283
But why are you hiding this from Mom?

362
00:20:59,283 --> 00:21:00,550
She should know too.

363
00:21:02,183 --> 00:21:03,750
Your mother has spent her whole life...

364
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:06,050
supporting her children and husband.

365
00:21:06,950 --> 00:21:08,950
I don't want to disappoint her this late.

366
00:21:11,283 --> 00:21:13,550
There's still a lot I need to do.

367
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:17,650
Is it because of me?
Because I haven't settled down yet?

368
00:21:18,350 --> 00:21:20,016
No, it's not that.

369
00:21:20,016 --> 00:21:24,250
When I get a proper job again,
I'll tell her then.

370
00:21:25,783 --> 00:21:27,550
Until then, it's absolutely a secret
from your mom, okay?

371
00:21:30,383 --> 00:21:34,183
But you wear a suit every morning,

372
00:21:34,983 --> 00:21:36,083
so what about your clothes?

373
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:37,083
Well...

374
00:21:38,383 --> 00:21:40,950
I keep them in a subway locker...

375
00:21:42,650 --> 00:21:46,150
and change after work.

376
00:21:48,050 --> 00:21:49,050
Dad...

377
00:21:53,450 --> 00:21:55,583
Parents shouldn't make
their children worry.

378
00:22:00,683 --> 00:22:01,750
I'm sorry, Eun Ae.

379
00:22:09,950 --> 00:22:12,250
Why do you keep saying sorry?

380
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:16,050
I didn't even know
you were struggling alone,

381
00:22:17,883 --> 00:22:19,450
and I just keep causing trouble.

382
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:23,450
Why are you crying, you silly girl?

383
00:22:23,983 --> 00:22:25,550
I'm really okay.

384
00:22:26,383 --> 00:22:27,450
Don't cry.

385
00:22:28,283 --> 00:22:30,950
Here, stop crying and have a drink.

386
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:34,050
Eun Ae, if you drink this in one go,

387
00:22:34,383 --> 00:22:36,183
your stress will disappear.

388
00:22:36,183 --> 00:22:37,350
Here, drink.

389
00:22:37,850 --> 00:22:39,250
My daughter, my beautiful daughter.

390
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:41,150
Stop crying.

391
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:01,783
Cho Eun Hyeong,
what have you been doing all this time?

392
00:23:03,283 --> 00:23:05,850
At my age,
Father had already raised three children.

393
00:23:11,983 --> 00:23:14,250
What? Did you two eat together?

394
00:23:15,583 --> 00:23:17,250
I had a drink with my daughter
at a street stall.

395
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:18,483
It's been a while, you know.

396
00:23:19,783 --> 00:23:22,050
That's unfair. I like street stalls too.

397
00:23:22,050 --> 00:23:23,150
Why did you leave me out?

398
00:23:23,450 --> 00:23:25,883
Sorry, I'll invite you next time.

399
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:28,083
I don't like being invited after the fact.

400
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:31,250
No, Mom, it just happened today.

401
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:34,950
Next time, I'll treat both of you
to a full street stall course.

402
00:23:35,550 --> 00:23:36,583
I'll hold you to that.

403
00:23:36,583 --> 00:23:39,983
Since your investment went through,
you'll be getting paid now, right?

404
00:23:40,150 --> 00:23:43,350
Of course.

405
00:23:44,350 --> 00:23:46,850
Let's go inside.
You should go up and rest too.

406
00:23:46,850 --> 00:23:49,650
- Yes. Good night.
- Good night.

407
00:23:49,950 --> 00:23:51,150
- Let's go in.
- Did you look into your vacation?

408
00:23:51,150 --> 00:23:52,550
You can take about ten days off, right?

409
00:23:52,550 --> 00:23:55,383
I was so busy today, I forgot.

410
00:23:55,383 --> 00:23:56,750
Sorry.

411
00:24:03,450 --> 00:24:04,750
Charging. 200 joules, 300 joules.

412
00:24:07,783 --> 00:24:09,750
Starting CPR. Step back.

413
00:24:09,950 --> 00:24:11,350
One, two, three, four.

414
00:24:15,183 --> 00:24:16,983
- What are you doing?
- Epinephrine, one milligram.

415
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:18,650
One, two, three, four.

416
00:24:18,883 --> 00:24:20,450
One, two, three, four.

417
00:24:20,450 --> 00:24:22,650
You startled me! Eun Ae.

418
00:24:23,150 --> 00:24:24,250
What are you doing?

419
00:24:25,850 --> 00:24:28,750
"The ER Witch?" Isn't that a web novel?

420
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:32,583
Yeah, it is.

421
00:24:33,250 --> 00:24:34,250
Why are you reading that?

422
00:24:35,683 --> 00:24:37,650
A friend of a friend asked me...

423
00:24:37,650 --> 00:24:39,650
to do some consulting for a web novel.

424
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:42,750
But I got too into it.

425
00:24:46,050 --> 00:24:47,850
Why? What?

426
00:24:48,450 --> 00:24:51,150
Your exam is coming up soon,
and you're this relaxed?

427
00:24:52,283 --> 00:24:54,683
I know, I shouldn't be doing this.

428
00:24:57,850 --> 00:24:59,750
Get a grip.

429
00:25:00,250 --> 00:25:02,150
If you disappoint Mom too...

430
00:25:03,450 --> 00:25:04,450
What are you saying?

431
00:25:04,850 --> 00:25:07,483
Get out. Can't you see I'm studying?

432
00:25:07,950 --> 00:25:08,950
Work hard.

433
00:25:22,850 --> 00:25:23,850
It's uploaded.

434
00:25:23,983 --> 00:25:26,850
Fresh Chapter Five of "The ER Witch."

435
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:30,250
Yes! I'm number one. Let me read.

436
00:25:34,883 --> 00:25:35,883
Wait.

437
00:25:39,250 --> 00:25:40,850
What is this? Why does it feel so real?

438
00:25:42,483 --> 00:25:44,850
This writer is a genius.

439
00:25:45,083 --> 00:25:46,250
(Kangsu Construction)

440
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:48,350
It started and stopped!

441
00:25:48,350 --> 00:25:51,650
The CPO must take responsibility!

442
00:25:59,450 --> 00:26:00,650
You finally came out.

443
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:03,583
There was
a small misunderstanding yesterday.

444
00:26:03,883 --> 00:26:06,550
I sincerely apologize
for causing a disturbance.

445
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:11,150
You look a bit swollen. I'm sorry.

446
00:26:12,883 --> 00:26:14,550
- It's you again!
- It's okay.

447
00:26:14,750 --> 00:26:16,850
I have something to discuss with her,
so please get back to work.

448
00:26:17,050 --> 00:26:18,283
- Is that okay?
- Yes.

449
00:26:23,750 --> 00:26:27,250
Then it seems you're ready to talk.

450
00:26:27,883 --> 00:26:28,883
Shall we begin?

451
00:26:30,483 --> 00:26:32,150
Please give Joy back to me.

452
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:33,150
Just a moment.

453
00:26:33,550 --> 00:26:36,950
Before that,
I'm not the CPO you're trying to talk to.

454
00:26:37,750 --> 00:26:40,150
- What?
- I'm not the CPO.

455
00:26:41,783 --> 00:26:43,950
You said you'd talk,
and now you're brushing me off?

456
00:26:44,583 --> 00:26:46,850
If you act like that,
I have no choice either.

457
00:26:47,050 --> 00:26:49,350
- An eye for an eye, a sword for a sword.
- Look.

458
00:26:49,383 --> 00:26:52,650
If you act like a thug,
I'll have to act like one too.

459
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:54,850
- Give me back my baby.
- What?

460
00:26:54,850 --> 00:26:56,483
Joy is my child
that I created and raised...

461
00:26:56,483 --> 00:26:58,450
and brought into this world.

462
00:26:58,450 --> 00:26:59,750
So give her back.

463
00:27:00,150 --> 00:27:01,850
I don't need money or anything else.

464
00:27:01,850 --> 00:27:04,950
Just give me back my baby, Joy. Please.

465
00:27:04,950 --> 00:27:08,583
Look,
I have nothing to do with Joy or whatever.

466
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:11,850
Give her back!

467
00:27:12,350 --> 00:27:15,750
Give me back my baby!

468
00:27:16,483 --> 00:27:19,250
- Give me back my baby.
- What's going on?

469
00:27:19,550 --> 00:27:21,250
- Give me back my baby.
- Did that man dump her?

470
00:27:21,650 --> 00:27:22,850
- What's happening?
- That's my baby.

471
00:27:23,250 --> 00:27:24,683
- That's not it.
- Give me back.

472
00:27:25,150 --> 00:27:27,183
- Give me back my baby!
- That's not it.

473
00:27:27,483 --> 00:27:28,850
- Please.
- I told you, it's not me.

474
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:30,450
Give me back!

475
00:27:30,450 --> 00:27:34,650
Give me back my baby!

476
00:27:34,650 --> 00:27:35,650
What's with this woman?

477
00:27:57,150 --> 00:27:59,783
(Our Happy Days)

478
00:27:59,950 --> 00:28:01,850
What? A legal notice?

479
00:28:01,850 --> 00:28:03,650
Assault, obstruction of business,

480
00:28:03,650 --> 00:28:05,283
trespassing, property damage,

481
00:28:05,283 --> 00:28:06,950
- defamation.
- Give it back!

482
00:28:07,083 --> 00:28:08,650
Make a position for Seong Jun.

483
00:28:08,650 --> 00:28:10,383
- Ko Dae Chi.
- Stop it.

484
00:28:10,950 --> 00:28:12,783
This is completely hopeless.

485
00:28:13,450 --> 00:28:14,883
You said it was a lucky charm.

486
00:28:15,050 --> 00:28:17,650
Give me luck,

487
00:28:17,783 --> 00:28:19,450
please!

488
00:28:20,250 --> 00:28:21,850
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
